WEBVTT

00:03.873 --> 00:04.221
.

00:06.963 --> 00:09.139
♪

00:09.183 --> 00:10.575
- I told them that
she can stay with us.

00:10.619 --> 00:12.055
- You can't trust her.
- Look, I'm sorry,

00:12.099 --> 00:13.448
but she's coming home with us.

00:13.491 --> 00:16.277
- No, Ethan,
she's going home with you.

00:22.326 --> 00:25.155
- This is Gwen Garrett,
our new COO.

00:25.199 --> 00:29.159
We never had an old COO.

00:29.203 --> 00:31.248
- If we lose one girl,
we lose them both.

00:31.292 --> 00:32.815
- BSD is repaired.

00:32.858 --> 00:34.860
- You got an offer tonight,
didn't you?

00:34.904 --> 00:36.123
- Mayo Clinic.

00:36.166 --> 00:37.994
- Of course,
you're going to take it.

00:41.563 --> 00:43.173
- You're suggesting
I'm a murderer.

00:43.217 --> 00:44.305
- You know what's the
most fascinating thing

00:44.348 --> 00:45.480
about serial killers?

00:45.523 --> 00:47.221
They all can't seem to resist

00:47.264 --> 00:50.006
taking a personal item
from their victims.

00:51.877 --> 00:53.705
- Oh, oh, no, Bob.

00:53.749 --> 00:57.100
♪

01:02.410 --> 01:04.847
- We need a crash cart.
Crash cart, now!

01:04.890 --> 01:07.284
We need a crash cart in here.

01:07.328 --> 01:10.113
- There's no pulse.
- Take over compressions.

01:10.157 --> 01:12.202
- Start bagging.

01:14.509 --> 01:16.337
- Charged to 200.
Clear!

01:16.380 --> 01:17.773
- Clear!

01:17.816 --> 01:22.038
- Resume compressions.
Charged to 200.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.345
Clear.

01:24.388 --> 01:26.912
Resume compressions.
- We need to talk.

01:26.956 --> 01:29.089
- Charge to 200.

01:35.138 --> 01:42.363
♪

01:48.804 --> 01:50.284
- This way.

01:54.810 --> 01:57.378
This is my father's.

01:57.421 --> 01:59.728
- Appreciate your help,
Dr. Reese.

02:10.652 --> 02:12.741
Forensics will gather samples
to collect for DNA,

02:12.784 --> 02:14.177
but they may need
to take a few of

02:14.221 --> 02:15.744
your father's things
to the lab.

02:15.787 --> 02:17.224
- I understand.

02:20.270 --> 02:22.446
♪

02:22.490 --> 02:24.579
- I know that this isn't easy,

02:24.622 --> 02:27.625
but...but it's
the right thing to do.

02:27.669 --> 02:30.889
- You're the last person
to tell me what's right.

02:34.893 --> 02:41.422
♪

02:45.208 --> 02:46.775
- Sharon.
- Yo.

02:46.818 --> 02:48.559
- Have you heard
from Dr. Reese?

02:48.603 --> 02:51.867
- She's your resident.
Why would she call me?

02:51.910 --> 02:53.825
- Well, she's due back today,
but I was expecting her

02:53.869 --> 02:55.436
at rounds first thing
this morning.

02:55.479 --> 02:57.220
- Well, she hasn't
been in touch.

02:57.264 --> 02:59.831
Let's hope she's okay.

02:59.875 --> 03:04.184
But don't you need to address
our new med students?

03:04.227 --> 03:06.273
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

03:10.102 --> 03:11.974
- Ladies and gentleman,
this is Dr. Charles.

03:12.017 --> 03:16.326
He's our Chief of Psychiatry.
- Good morning, and welcome.

03:16.370 --> 03:18.720
First thing I want to
tell you about is...

03:23.855 --> 03:26.554
- Yeah, yeah.

03:26.597 --> 03:28.904
Our days of butting heads
are almost over.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.819
- Oh, thank God for that.

03:34.083 --> 03:36.520
By the way, did you know that
Rochester, Minnesota,

03:36.564 --> 03:38.914
is the 14th coldest city
in the U.S.?

03:38.957 --> 03:42.047
And Chicago's 48, you know.
It's much warmer.

03:42.091 --> 03:45.094
You don't want me to go.

03:45.137 --> 03:47.662
- Oh, please.
- Oh, you're going to miss me.

03:47.705 --> 03:51.361
- Miss the most egotistical,
ambitious, and arrogant

03:51.405 --> 03:54.669
man I've ever met?
Hardly.

03:54.712 --> 03:55.844
- Here.

03:55.887 --> 03:58.238
Now that you
are a big shot attending,

03:58.281 --> 03:59.891
I'm going to leave you
with this.

03:59.935 --> 04:03.373
"Cardiac surgeons
fix broken hearts."

04:08.770 --> 04:15.559
♪

04:15.603 --> 04:18.562
- We could have had something.

04:20.564 --> 04:23.524
- You're the one who's leaving.

04:23.567 --> 04:25.700
- Dr. Bekker, Dr. Rhodes.
They need you in the E.D.

04:25.743 --> 04:28.442
Suspected TRA coming in.
- Yeah.

04:36.493 --> 04:38.365
- Trevor Keyes,
high-speed decelerating

04:38.408 --> 04:40.367
motor vehicle crash.
Prolonged extrication.

04:40.410 --> 04:43.283
Right arm BP 136/88.
Nothing in his left.

04:43.326 --> 04:44.632
Wife was treated on the scene.

04:44.675 --> 04:46.373
- Mr. Keyes, do you know
where you are?

04:46.416 --> 04:49.332
Can you squeeze my hand?
All right, minimal response.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.029
Let's transfer him on my count.

04:53.031 --> 04:55.556
One, two, three.

04:55.599 --> 04:58.080
- All right,
let's go.

04:59.821 --> 05:03.172
- Okay, Mr. Keyes, can you
touch your chin to your chest?

05:03.215 --> 05:04.608
Any pain?
- No.

05:04.652 --> 05:07.002
- No.

05:07.045 --> 05:08.438
- Good, c-spine is cleared.

05:08.482 --> 05:09.874
Let's get a chest x-ray stat.
Logroll.

05:09.918 --> 05:11.833
- Dr. Bekker and Dr. Rhodes.

05:11.876 --> 05:13.400
They're
cardiothoracic surgeons.

05:13.443 --> 05:15.445
- X-ray clear.
- This is his wife.

05:15.489 --> 05:17.621
- Linda.
Please, help my husband.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.449
- There's weakness in
Mr. Keyes' left hand,

05:19.493 --> 05:21.277
and it's cold.

05:22.887 --> 05:24.976
- Wide mediastinum.

05:25.020 --> 05:26.804
- There is a
high probability of a

05:26.848 --> 05:28.676
contained rupture in his aorta.

05:28.719 --> 05:30.547
- We need to get Mr. Keyes
to the hybrid room right away.

05:30.591 --> 05:31.809
- Okay.
- All right, let's go.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.463
Have anesthesia
meet us upstairs,

05:33.507 --> 05:35.160
and bring esmolol for the road.
- Right away.

05:38.207 --> 05:42.037
♪

05:42.080 --> 05:44.518
- Don't worry, baby.
It's gonna be all right.

05:44.561 --> 05:46.650
It's gonna be all right.
- Out of the way.

05:46.694 --> 05:48.304
Out of the way!
Everybody out.

05:48.348 --> 05:49.653
Out, out, out, out!

05:49.697 --> 05:51.568
Come on, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.182
Linda.

05:59.707 --> 06:01.448
- Linda.

06:02.536 --> 06:05.408
I love you.
- Trev, I love you, too.

06:05.452 --> 06:10.370
But you're gonna be fine.
- I--

06:10.413 --> 06:12.415
Trevor?

06:12.459 --> 06:14.591
- Nothing.

06:14.635 --> 06:16.680
- No pulse.
- Trevor.

06:16.724 --> 06:19.117
Oh, God.
- Come on.

06:20.902 --> 06:23.513
Oh, God, Trevor.

06:23.557 --> 06:24.862
- Let's go.
- Wrong floor.

06:24.906 --> 06:26.168
This isn't surgery.
- Can't wait.

06:26.211 --> 06:27.474
Got to open his chest now.

06:27.517 --> 06:29.606
♪

06:29.650 --> 06:31.521
Get me a scalpel.
- Connor.

06:31.565 --> 06:33.654
- Check his pulse.

06:34.481 --> 06:36.613
- No.
What's happening to him?

06:36.657 --> 06:38.398
- His aorta ruptured.
I've got to get control.

06:38.441 --> 06:40.051
- Here.

06:43.620 --> 06:46.536
- Trevor, no, no!

06:46.580 --> 06:48.799
No!

06:51.236 --> 06:53.108
- Help me spread his ribs.

06:55.937 --> 06:57.460
♪

06:59.897 --> 07:02.987
- There's too much blood.
- Oh, God.

07:05.947 --> 07:09.211
- His aorta is wide open.

07:11.126 --> 07:15.217
- I'm so sorry.
There's nothing I can do.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.958
- He's gone.

07:17.001 --> 07:19.047
- I'm sorry.

07:19.090 --> 07:22.093
Trevor's dead?

07:22.137 --> 07:24.313
No!

07:24.356 --> 07:28.143
No, Trevor, no!
No!

07:28.186 --> 07:30.188
Trevor, no!

07:33.453 --> 07:36.499
- Time of death, 8:23.

07:39.546 --> 07:46.770
♪

07:51.383 --> 07:51.558
.

07:51.601 --> 07:53.951
- We shouldn't
have lost the patient.

07:53.995 --> 07:55.083
- His aorta burst.
What could you have done?

07:55.126 --> 07:56.519
- When we were in the E.D.,

07:56.563 --> 07:58.129
he hadn't yet suffered
the fatal rupture.

07:58.173 --> 07:59.740
If we'd been able
to repair his injury there,

07:59.783 --> 08:01.045
he'd still be alive.

08:01.089 --> 08:02.307
The problem was
the time it took

08:02.351 --> 08:03.874
transferring him upstairs.

08:03.918 --> 08:05.485
- But the E.D.
isn't equipped to perform

08:05.528 --> 08:07.617
the kind of procedure
you're talking about.

08:07.661 --> 08:09.967
- That's Dr. Rhodes's point.
- There needs to be

08:10.011 --> 08:12.579
a hybrid operating room
in the E.D.

08:12.622 --> 08:15.843
Fully equipped to perform
emergency cardiac surgery.

08:15.886 --> 08:17.975
- An O.R. in the E.D.

08:18.019 --> 08:19.760
- We have lost
far too many patients

08:19.803 --> 08:21.762
on the way to the O.R.

08:21.805 --> 08:25.592
- Actually, I like the idea,

08:25.635 --> 08:29.552
but converting a trauma room
into a surgical suite--

08:29.596 --> 08:32.250
it's not an
inexpensive proposition.

08:33.643 --> 08:37.386
I'll tell you what.
Write up a proposal.

08:37.429 --> 08:39.127
- I'll have it on your desk
in an hour.

08:39.170 --> 08:41.651
- Dr. Rhodes,
with your background

08:41.695 --> 08:46.134
in both trauma and CT,
you'd be the ideal person

08:46.177 --> 08:48.310
to head a program like this.

08:48.353 --> 08:51.443
If the board okays it,
I'd like you to stay.

08:51.487 --> 08:53.794
- I'm sorry, Ms. Goodwin,
but I start

08:53.837 --> 08:55.535
at the Mayo Clinic on Monday.

09:08.939 --> 09:11.072
- Hey.

09:11.115 --> 09:15.250
- That looks so good on you.
- I agree.

09:15.293 --> 09:17.513
- You know, we should
get serious about a date.

09:17.557 --> 09:20.255
Book a venue.

09:20.298 --> 09:22.866
I was thinking more of like
a city hall-type thing.

09:22.910 --> 09:25.434
I don't know, a few friends.
Maybe dinner after.

09:25.477 --> 09:28.132
- What, no, I already talked
to Father Brady.

09:28.176 --> 09:30.091
He promised us a Saturday
at St. Ursula's.

09:30.134 --> 09:31.875
Man, I got a whole neighborhood
to invite.

09:31.919 --> 09:33.224
We need a hall.

09:33.268 --> 09:35.096
- Dr. Manning,
Dr. Halstead, with me.

09:35.139 --> 09:37.185
- Okay.

09:37.228 --> 09:39.666
- 25-year-old deaf male

09:39.709 --> 09:41.015
Peter Rush.

09:41.058 --> 09:42.669
Intractable headache,
disoriented.

09:42.712 --> 09:44.671
Sensitivity to light.
GCS 15.

09:44.714 --> 09:47.543
Vomited times two in the ambo.

09:47.587 --> 09:48.544
- Yep.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.894
- Would you like
an interpreter?

09:50.938 --> 09:53.375
- Yes.
- She's certified.

09:55.290 --> 09:57.858
- Let's sheet transfer.
One, two, three.

09:57.901 --> 10:01.296
- Heart rate 112,
BP 122/76.

10:01.339 --> 10:05.256
Normal sinus rhythm.
- These two take care of you.

10:05.300 --> 10:08.042
This is his fiancée, Bonnie.

10:08.085 --> 10:09.609
♪

10:09.652 --> 10:12.002
- Have you been deaf
since birth?

10:12.046 --> 10:14.352
- No, 14. Mumps.

10:16.093 --> 10:18.530
- She says he had
cochlear implant surgery

10:18.574 --> 10:20.663
a month ago.
It's due to be activated.

10:20.707 --> 10:23.884
- Chest is clear,
regular rate rhythm S1 and 2.

10:23.927 --> 10:25.886
- Sick!

10:27.496 --> 10:29.890
- And let's give him four
milligrams of ondansetron.

10:29.933 --> 10:31.718
- Got it.

10:33.154 --> 10:35.417
- She says it's meningitis
from the implant.

10:35.460 --> 10:36.766
She warned him not to get it.

10:36.810 --> 10:38.246
- We don't know
that he has meningitis.

10:38.289 --> 10:39.639
His neck exam is normal.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.858
- And meningitis can occur
after surgery,

10:41.902 --> 10:43.904
but it's not common.

10:43.947 --> 10:45.122
Let's get a CBC, BMP,

10:45.166 --> 10:47.124
and cultures times two.
- Right.

10:47.168 --> 10:48.909
- And let's send him up
for a head CT.

10:48.952 --> 10:50.432
- Okay, I'll put in the order.

10:50.475 --> 10:52.782
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

10:54.479 --> 10:55.393
- April.

10:55.437 --> 10:57.787
Hey, April, can I get a second?

11:00.660 --> 11:03.097
Emily's really
turned her life around.

11:03.140 --> 11:06.056
She's clean, going to AA.

11:06.100 --> 11:07.928
She's got a job,
sells cosmetics.

11:07.971 --> 11:09.320
- And you're
telling me this why?

11:09.364 --> 11:11.018
- I'm bringing Emily
to Conner's party,

11:11.061 --> 11:13.368
and she'd like to talk to you.

11:13.411 --> 11:15.892
- She feels bad.

11:15.936 --> 11:18.765
- She should.

11:18.808 --> 11:23.944
- Emily wants to make amends.
It's a part of the program.

11:23.987 --> 11:27.730
- Emily has a drug problem
and a gambling problem.

11:27.774 --> 11:29.471
She stole opioids
from the hospital,

11:29.514 --> 11:31.473
- I know.
- She needs to be in rehab.

11:31.516 --> 11:32.735
- I--
- She needs psychotherapy--

11:32.779 --> 11:35.825
- I know.
But she's really trying.

11:38.523 --> 11:41.613
One step at a time.

11:44.878 --> 11:46.270
- Mr. Jackson,

11:46.314 --> 11:48.229
these are student doctors,
Curry and McNeal.

11:48.272 --> 11:49.578
They're going to help me
sew you up.

11:49.621 --> 11:51.667
- Okay.
- McNeal, glove up.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.321
Curry, why don't you
get him an IV

11:53.364 --> 11:54.714
and hang a bag
of normal saline?

11:54.757 --> 11:57.673
- That's a nurse's job.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.457
- I said,
that's a nurse's job.

11:59.501 --> 12:01.285
- Every doctor should know
how to put in an IV.

12:01.329 --> 12:02.896
- I do know how,
but I don't see the point.

12:02.939 --> 12:04.375
That's not something
I'm ever going to be doing.

12:04.419 --> 12:05.681
I'm not going into
patient care.

12:05.725 --> 12:09.076
- No, sir.

12:09.119 --> 12:12.601
Ms. Curry, when you are
on my service,

12:12.644 --> 12:14.821
you will do exactly
what's expected of you.

12:14.864 --> 12:16.561
Do you understand?

12:19.260 --> 12:21.262
Mr. Jackson is a machinist,

12:21.305 --> 12:22.829
and he cut his forearm
in the shop.

12:22.872 --> 12:26.049
What do you make of the wound?
- Mm, pretty clean.

12:26.093 --> 12:28.748
Edges are smooth.
Nylon suture?

12:28.791 --> 12:30.837
- You'd better
take another look.

12:32.142 --> 12:34.362
- Oh.

12:34.405 --> 12:36.016
That's actually
a pretty deep cut.

12:36.059 --> 12:37.800
- So how do you obliterate
the dead space?

12:37.844 --> 12:41.195
- Um...
- Absorbable stitch.

12:41.238 --> 12:44.720
- Right, right.

12:44.764 --> 12:48.245
- Medical student.

12:49.203 --> 12:50.726
- You're a big guy.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.684
What's the matter,
couldn't play football?

12:55.209 --> 12:57.428
Let's numb that arm.

12:59.691 --> 13:03.826
- You don't have meningitis.

13:05.219 --> 13:07.264
- On the other hand,
we don't know why

13:07.308 --> 13:09.658
you're having these symptoms.

13:10.702 --> 13:13.575
- Your sensitivity to light
concerns us,

13:13.618 --> 13:15.795
so we'd like to do
some more blood work,

13:15.838 --> 13:19.799
including a genetic test,
just to cover our bases.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.757
You'll have to
stay here overnight.

13:21.801 --> 13:25.021
We'll try to find you
a bed upstairs.

13:25.065 --> 13:26.544
Otherwise, we will make you

13:26.588 --> 13:28.938
as comfortable
as possible down here.

13:28.982 --> 13:31.723
- The good news is we've
talked to your audiologist,

13:31.767 --> 13:34.465
and we can turn on
your cochlear implant.

13:37.207 --> 13:39.427
- Yes, I want it.
Thank you.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.170
♪

13:43.213 --> 13:45.346
Yes, I'm doing it.

13:47.739 --> 13:49.480
- They're having an argument.
- Yeah.

13:49.524 --> 13:51.482
- Maybe we should step out.

13:54.529 --> 13:57.924
♪

14:11.459 --> 14:11.851
.

14:20.163 --> 14:23.471
Dr. Reese, there you are.

14:23.514 --> 14:27.649
I am very glad to see you.
- I'm not staying.

14:27.692 --> 14:30.913
I'm leaving Med. I'm continuing
my residency at Baylor.

14:30.957 --> 14:33.263
- Oh.
- I think people here

14:33.307 --> 14:36.397
would, uh, always
look at me and think,

14:36.440 --> 14:37.615
oh, there's that doctor,

14:37.659 --> 14:39.966
the one whose father
murdered those girls.

14:40.009 --> 14:43.317
I could live with that.

14:43.360 --> 14:46.059
It's you.

14:46.102 --> 14:48.061
- All that time

14:48.104 --> 14:51.803
you suspected my father,
you never told me anything.

14:51.847 --> 14:54.067
- Sarah, look,
I was trying to protect you

14:54.110 --> 14:56.112
until I was absolutely certain.
I mean, surely--

14:56.156 --> 14:58.854
- I can't trust you.
I can never trust you.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.508
- You have every right
to be upset,

15:00.551 --> 15:03.511
and I hope that we have
some time to talk through this,

15:03.554 --> 15:05.121
but please, don't leave.

15:05.165 --> 15:09.821
- Every time I'd see your face,
I would remember...

15:09.865 --> 15:15.436
when I walked into that room
and saw my father on the floor.

15:16.872 --> 15:18.918
I--

15:18.961 --> 15:21.181
I saw it in your eyes.

15:23.183 --> 15:25.881
You were going to
let him die.

15:48.512 --> 15:49.557
- Hi.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.734
- Hi, Peter,
this is Helen Moore,

15:52.777 --> 15:54.431
the hospital's audiologist.

15:54.475 --> 15:59.393
- So, let me get this on you,
and then I can activate it.

16:03.310 --> 16:05.355
- No.

16:08.097 --> 16:10.708
I don't want it.
- I--I don't understand.

16:10.752 --> 16:15.539
- Bonnie, she think because
of this, I don't love her.

16:15.583 --> 16:16.888
♪

16:16.932 --> 16:19.500
I want Bonnie
more than my hearing.

16:20.718 --> 16:23.983
- If you change your mind,
let your doctors know.

16:30.946 --> 16:32.295
Yeah, I've seen this before.

16:32.339 --> 16:34.645
Implants are controversial
among the deaf.

16:34.689 --> 16:39.607
For Bonnie, deafness
is a culture, a community.

16:39.650 --> 16:42.566
She thinks we're trying to fix
a problem that isn't a problem.

16:49.443 --> 16:51.575
- 45-year-old female.

16:51.619 --> 16:54.491
Found delusional and agitated.
- Put her in treatment 4.

16:54.535 --> 16:56.885
- No obvious injuries,
no meds given in the field.

16:56.928 --> 16:59.018
- All right,
get ready to rotate.

16:59.061 --> 17:01.411
Take them in, Angel.
Dr. Choi?

17:01.455 --> 17:03.805
- Can't leave this GSW.
Terry, start the work-up.

17:03.848 --> 17:05.589
See if you can get a history.
I'll be there soon.

17:05.633 --> 17:07.200
- I'm going to call Psych.
Where's Monique?

17:07.243 --> 17:08.810
Monique, get in here.

17:13.293 --> 17:15.208
- Let's transfer on my count.
- It's his fault.

17:15.251 --> 17:17.514
It's his fault!
- One, two, three.

17:18.863 --> 17:20.865
- Ma'am, can you
tell us your name?

17:20.909 --> 17:22.258
Do you know where you are?

17:22.302 --> 17:24.521
- Over there. Look.
It's his fault.

17:24.565 --> 17:26.262
- We need to sedate her.
- It's his fault.

17:26.306 --> 17:28.047
It's his fault.
- You should wait for Dr. Choi.

17:28.090 --> 17:30.484
- He told me to work her up.
I can't with her like this.

17:30.527 --> 17:33.095
10 of haloperidol.
- Stop it before it's too late.

17:35.228 --> 17:37.273
Stop him. Stop.
Stop him before it's too late.

17:37.317 --> 17:38.492
Stop him before
it's too late.

17:38.535 --> 17:40.059
Stop him
before it's too late.

17:40.102 --> 17:41.495
Stop him before...
it's too late.

17:43.932 --> 17:45.107
- Let's let her calm down

17:45.151 --> 17:47.109
before we
take off the restraints.

17:50.156 --> 17:52.201
- I thought this patient
was agitated.

17:52.245 --> 17:54.464
- She was.
I sedated her.

17:54.508 --> 17:58.077
Without waiting for me?

17:58.120 --> 18:01.819
- Well, I couldn't examine her.
- Well now, neither can I.

18:01.863 --> 18:03.125
You're a medical student.

18:03.169 --> 18:04.431
You're not authorized
to order medication.

18:04.474 --> 18:06.128
- But she was
delusional, psychotic.

18:06.172 --> 18:07.869
- And you are not qualified
to make that diagnosis,

18:07.912 --> 18:09.479
or any diagnosis.

18:09.523 --> 18:11.002
The patient's emotional state
could have been

18:11.046 --> 18:12.656
something entirely physical,
and therefore

18:12.700 --> 18:15.224
easily treatable,
like a UTI, for instance.

18:15.268 --> 18:16.834
But now,
we can't determine that

18:16.878 --> 18:18.140
because you knocked her out.

18:18.184 --> 18:19.837
You ought to
be written up for this.

18:19.881 --> 18:21.491
- Dr. Charles, it was--

18:21.535 --> 18:22.536
- I'm right here.

18:22.579 --> 18:24.842
- Supervise your
medical students!

18:27.889 --> 18:31.545
♪

18:35.157 --> 18:37.551
- I wasn't told
the board was in session.

18:37.594 --> 18:41.381
- Dr. Rhodes,
impressive proposal.

18:41.424 --> 18:44.297
Unfortunately, we have to pass.

18:44.340 --> 18:50.172
- A C-Arm. That's anywhere
from 1.7 million to 2.5.

18:50.216 --> 18:53.697
Uh, booms and lights, 200,000.

18:53.741 --> 18:56.396
Two large ceiling-mounted
hi-def screens.

18:56.439 --> 18:59.050
Do I need to continue?
- No hospital I know of

18:59.094 --> 19:02.358
has a hybrid O.R. in the E.D.

19:02.402 --> 19:05.144
Not to mention
the huge PR benefit

19:05.187 --> 19:06.449
in Med being the first--

19:06.493 --> 19:08.712
- The investment
is not worth the expense.

19:08.756 --> 19:11.062
I recommended
that the board pass.

19:11.106 --> 19:13.804
They agreed.

19:16.764 --> 19:19.114
- Well...

19:19.158 --> 19:21.290
thank you for trying.

19:26.252 --> 19:30.386
- I think it would be a mistake
for the hospital to lose this.

19:41.092 --> 19:41.223
.

19:41.267 --> 19:45.009
- In Yiddish, "bon voyage"
is for gezunterhait.

19:45.053 --> 19:47.751
In Hebrew, however,
we say leich l'shalom,

19:47.795 --> 19:50.319
which literally means
"go towards peace,"

19:50.363 --> 19:52.800
but it has a deeper meaning

19:52.843 --> 19:56.151
of going towards
greater spiritual perfection.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.502
I'd like to wish you that,
Dr. Rhodes.

19:59.546 --> 20:01.896
Leich l'shalom.

20:06.857 --> 20:09.556
♪

20:09.599 --> 20:12.863
- April.
- Emily.

20:13.777 --> 20:18.173
- I want to apologize
for everything that happened.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.609
It was all my fault.

20:19.653 --> 20:23.265
I'm trying to make up
for what I did.

20:23.309 --> 20:26.573
I'm trying to
turn my life around, and...

20:26.616 --> 20:28.488
a lot of that
is because of you.

20:28.531 --> 20:31.099
You believed in me, and...

20:31.142 --> 20:34.102
I'm--I'm really sorry
I disappointed you.

20:36.147 --> 20:38.193
Be right back.

20:48.986 --> 20:51.206
- There you go.
- Thank you.

20:54.253 --> 20:57.299
- Did you get a chance
to check out that venue?

20:57.343 --> 20:58.866
- No.

20:58.909 --> 21:01.738
I'm sorry, I left it
at the hospital.

21:01.782 --> 21:05.655
- Yeah, well, I brought it.
- Oh.

21:08.876 --> 21:10.181
- Natalie, look,
if you don't want

21:10.225 --> 21:12.358
to get married, just say so.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.142
Where is this coming from?

21:14.185 --> 21:16.187
- You don't seem to care
about the ceremony,

21:16.231 --> 21:19.713
or the reception.
It took you a week to say yes.

21:19.756 --> 21:21.280
- And I said yes,
and I meant it.

21:21.323 --> 21:23.630
- But you act like our marriage
is no big deal.

21:23.673 --> 21:25.719
- Of course it's a big deal.

21:25.762 --> 21:29.026
But a church wedding,
a reception.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.680
I've done all that before.

21:30.724 --> 21:32.160
- I haven't
been married before.

21:32.203 --> 21:35.076
I want the whole thing.
- Just so you know,

21:35.119 --> 21:37.644
a wedding is not a marriage.

21:37.687 --> 21:39.646
- Glad you
cleared that up for me.

21:39.689 --> 21:40.951
- Will.
- No, I'm just

21:40.995 --> 21:42.823
overwhelmed with
your enthusiasm.

21:42.866 --> 21:44.868
I'm going to get some food.

21:50.178 --> 21:53.268
- Hey, Maggie.
Have you seen Ava?

21:56.532 --> 21:58.099
Ms. Goodwin.

21:58.142 --> 22:00.580
Hey, have you seen Dr. Bekker?

22:00.623 --> 22:01.885
She said she was
coming tonight.

22:01.929 --> 22:04.627
- Uh, no, I haven't.

22:04.671 --> 22:07.282
- Maybe she
got stuck in surgery.

22:07.326 --> 22:09.371
- Maybe.

22:15.159 --> 22:18.467
- So let's get four of the
flutes over here, one more.

22:18.511 --> 22:21.601
And then, we'll have a nice
arrangement right here.

22:21.644 --> 22:23.254
Great.

22:23.298 --> 22:26.257
- Dr. Bekker.

22:26.301 --> 22:29.173
- Of course, this way.
I'll be right back.

22:30.827 --> 22:32.786
- Creating a hybrid O.R.
in the E.D.

22:32.829 --> 22:35.354
would be expensive,
and the hospital

22:35.397 --> 22:37.138
is not willing
to make the commitment.

22:37.181 --> 22:39.923
However, if private donors
such as yourself

22:39.967 --> 22:42.099
would earmark contributions
for the project,

22:42.143 --> 22:45.494
the board would be incentivized
to make the investment.

22:45.538 --> 22:47.931
- Right.

22:50.020 --> 22:52.240
- I wouldn't expect
you personally

22:52.283 --> 22:54.721
to fund the entire project.

22:54.764 --> 22:57.071
I would think
with your connections,

22:57.114 --> 22:59.247
you could raise it with
just a few phone calls.

23:00.466 --> 23:01.989
Well...

23:02.032 --> 23:03.382
And you'd be running
this project?

23:03.425 --> 23:06.689
- No, Dr. Rhodes--
Connor will be.

23:06.733 --> 23:08.909
- I thought he was off
to the Mayo Clinic.

23:08.952 --> 23:10.258
- I believe he'll
stay in Chicago

23:10.301 --> 23:12.913
if the program gets funded.

23:12.956 --> 23:14.523
- Well, as I'm sure
you're aware,

23:14.567 --> 23:18.440
my son and I have not had
the easiest of relationships.

23:18.484 --> 23:20.747
I'd want my involvement
kept anonymous.

23:20.790 --> 23:22.662
- Of course, I understand.

23:24.620 --> 23:26.927
- Let me think about it.

23:26.970 --> 23:29.451
- I'm afraid this
is time-sensitive.

23:29.495 --> 23:30.974
- Oh.

23:31.018 --> 23:32.759
♪

23:32.802 --> 23:35.936
I have an idea.

23:35.979 --> 23:39.809
Why don't we go to dinner,
discuss this further?

23:53.344 --> 23:59.916
♪

24:51.402 --> 24:51.577
.

24:51.620 --> 24:54.797
- Hey, Peter Rush's
these test results.

24:56.146 --> 24:59.541
- Oh, man.
- Yeah.

25:12.815 --> 25:16.471
- Peter, your deafness
wasn't caused by mumps.

25:16.515 --> 25:18.168
It was caused
by a genetic disease

25:18.212 --> 25:21.607
that you tested positive for,
Usher syndrome.

25:21.650 --> 25:23.304
- And it's what caused
the symptoms

25:23.347 --> 25:25.654
you are now experiencing.

25:27.134 --> 25:30.006
- So some of your symptoms
can be addressed,

25:30.050 --> 25:33.096
but Usher syndrome
causes a condition

25:33.140 --> 25:35.272
called retinitis pigmentosa.

25:37.927 --> 25:40.582
A progressive deterioration
of eyesight.

25:40.626 --> 25:43.803
- I'm sorry, Peter,

25:43.846 --> 25:46.327
but retinitis pigmentosa
is untreatable.

25:46.370 --> 25:48.851
- No cure.

25:48.895 --> 25:52.638
I'm going blind?

25:52.681 --> 25:57.164
- Yes, you will experience
a significant loss in vision,

25:57.207 --> 25:59.732
and maybe even blindness.

25:59.775 --> 26:02.473
- Oh, God.

26:02.517 --> 26:04.650
- We know this is
a lot to process.

26:04.693 --> 26:07.740
A genetic disease specialist
will come down to discuss

26:07.783 --> 26:09.350
what you can expect,
and what measures

26:09.393 --> 26:11.700
can be taken to help.

26:13.920 --> 26:18.968
- Maybe you want Bonnie
to come here for that?

26:19.012 --> 26:21.014
- No, she can't find out.

26:21.057 --> 26:25.192
- But you're getting married.
She will find out.

26:25.235 --> 26:28.674
- She broke it off.

26:28.717 --> 26:32.025
Now, it's all for the best.

26:32.068 --> 26:35.594
I don't want her
coming back out of pity.

26:37.639 --> 26:39.206
- You don't--
- She should be with someone

26:39.249 --> 26:41.338
who won't be a burden to her.

26:47.475 --> 26:52.219
♪

26:55.526 --> 27:00.183
Sarah called.

27:00.227 --> 27:01.881
Asked me to send her stuff.

27:01.924 --> 27:05.232
She thought maybe she left
her case log here.

27:05.275 --> 27:08.061
- Oh, uh, yeah.
Um...

27:08.104 --> 27:11.630
Right here.

27:11.673 --> 27:15.677
- Okay.
You know, I really liked Sarah.

27:15.721 --> 27:19.812
I always hoped, you know,
something might happen, or...

27:19.855 --> 27:22.641
But I guess with all
that she was going through,

27:22.684 --> 27:26.427
never really had a real chance.
- Yeah.

27:26.470 --> 27:29.430
I'm sorry about that, Noah.

27:29.473 --> 27:32.520
- Yeah.

27:34.696 --> 27:37.699
You know, she once told me
that, um...

27:37.743 --> 27:42.704
the way you brought her
into psych helped her.

27:42.748 --> 27:45.968
That you were the dad
she always wanted.

27:46.012 --> 27:53.019
♪

28:23.571 --> 28:26.313
- Uh, I've just been dizzy,
a little tired.

28:26.356 --> 28:27.706
Getting these headaches.

28:27.749 --> 28:29.751
- She's also complaining
of diarrhea.

28:29.795 --> 28:32.536
Vitals are mostly normal,
a little soft on the pressure.

28:32.580 --> 28:35.975
BP 95/58, heart rate 110.

28:37.498 --> 28:40.588
- The patient is my sister,
so I'll leave you and April

28:40.631 --> 28:42.721
to do the exam.

28:42.764 --> 28:45.811
I'll be back to look in on you.
- Okay

28:50.032 --> 28:54.167
- What--right.

28:54.210 --> 28:56.212
I'm Elsa Curry,
third year medical student.

28:56.256 --> 28:58.214
I'm going to examine you.

29:07.006 --> 29:11.706
- Oh, um, no.
Um, I'm sorry.

29:11.750 --> 29:14.056
I'm sorry, uh...

29:14.100 --> 29:18.931
Peter's not up--for--

29:26.242 --> 29:28.157
Okay.

29:38.689 --> 29:40.691
Who told you?

29:40.735 --> 29:42.868
Did you?
- No, no.

29:42.911 --> 29:45.609
- No.

29:54.836 --> 29:56.882
- She wants to know why
Peter's acting like this.

29:56.925 --> 29:59.319
- It's up to Peter to tell her.

30:07.588 --> 30:10.330
- You can tell her.

30:10.373 --> 30:12.898
- Peter has a condition
called Usher syndrome,

30:12.941 --> 30:15.074
which caused him
to lose his hearing

30:15.117 --> 30:18.381
and will also cause him
to lose his sight.

30:21.428 --> 30:24.910
♪

30:44.407 --> 30:47.149
- All right, now,
let's move on to the budget.

30:47.193 --> 30:52.067
The first line item to discuss
is marketing and PR.

30:52.111 --> 30:56.028
Actually, let's table
that discussion.

30:56.071 --> 31:00.206
- Dr. Bekker, Dr. Rhodes,
thank you for joining us.

31:00.249 --> 31:01.816
I have good news.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.688
The hospital received
donations earmarked

31:04.732 --> 31:07.778
for your ED hybrid O.R.,
and the Board

31:07.822 --> 31:10.564
has decided to provide
matching funds.

31:10.607 --> 31:13.045
- We're going ahead
with your proposal.

31:13.088 --> 31:15.047
- Well, I am very happy
to hear that.

31:15.090 --> 31:19.138
- But there is one stipulation,
Dr. Rhodes.

31:19.181 --> 31:23.098
You have to stay
and run the program.

31:29.365 --> 31:32.064
- Emily's test results.

31:36.198 --> 31:38.026
- No.

31:39.593 --> 31:41.900
You're not sick.
You're pregnant.

31:46.382 --> 31:48.863
- You didn't suspect
that might be the case?

31:48.907 --> 31:51.997
- I mean, I have been
throwing up a lot.

31:52.040 --> 31:54.303
- Do you even know
who the father is?

31:54.347 --> 31:56.131
- Yeah, of course I know
who the father is.

31:56.175 --> 31:59.178
What do you think I am?
It's Bernie.

31:59.221 --> 32:02.442
- He's in my AA group.

32:02.485 --> 32:04.879
- You're not supposed to date

32:04.923 --> 32:06.576
people in your AA group.

32:06.620 --> 32:08.448
- Look, he's been sober
for six years.

32:08.491 --> 32:10.406
He's a responsible person.

32:10.450 --> 32:12.234
You call this responsible?

32:14.758 --> 32:16.935
I don't believe you.

32:18.893 --> 32:21.940
- Oh, God, I didn't
mean it to happen.

32:21.983 --> 32:24.812
What am I going to do now?

32:32.863 --> 32:33.038
.

32:33.081 --> 32:35.866
- Look, you were right.
Everything you said was right.

32:35.910 --> 32:37.477
I'm an idiot, a total idiot.
- Ethan, don't.

32:37.520 --> 32:39.131
You were just
trying to help her.

32:39.174 --> 32:40.523
You were trying to be
a good big brother.

32:40.567 --> 32:42.003
- And look at
the mess she's made.

32:42.047 --> 32:44.614
- I know.

32:44.658 --> 32:48.009
- Emily can't have this baby.

32:48.053 --> 32:50.316
- Come on.

32:50.359 --> 32:51.752
She has a history
of drug abuse.

32:51.795 --> 32:53.536
She's sleeping with some guy
in her AA group.

32:53.580 --> 32:54.929
- If you're going
where I think you're going--

32:54.973 --> 32:56.670
- April, two months ago,
Emily was homeless.

32:56.713 --> 32:58.541
Who know when
she'll run away again?

32:58.585 --> 33:01.544
She's completely unstable, and
she might start using again.

33:01.588 --> 33:03.764
Harm the fetus.
- And she might not.

33:03.807 --> 33:05.896
- What kind of life
can she give a child?

33:05.940 --> 33:07.637
- It doesn't matter.
- Of course it matters.

33:07.681 --> 33:11.685
- No.
You're not Catholic.

33:11.728 --> 33:16.255
It's a life.
We have to protect it.

33:26.482 --> 33:29.050
I want to apologize
for earlier.

33:29.094 --> 33:32.401
You really need to learn
how to follow protocol, okay?

33:32.445 --> 33:35.883
But I shouldn't have snapped
at you like that.

33:35.926 --> 33:40.888
I'm dealing with a, uh,
with a loss.

33:40.931 --> 33:42.977
- Thank you.

33:47.808 --> 33:49.070
- Coming in.

33:49.114 --> 33:51.203
And your paperwork is done.

33:51.246 --> 33:55.946
- I got to go tell Bernie.
I don't know how he'll take it.

33:55.990 --> 33:59.776
I hope he's happy,
but, God, what if he's not?

33:59.820 --> 34:01.300
I can't cope with this
by myself.

34:01.343 --> 34:03.258
I--I can't
have this baby alone.

34:03.302 --> 34:05.217
- Emily, you're not alone.

34:05.260 --> 34:07.045
- Oh, yeah, but Ethan's
so mad at me.

34:07.088 --> 34:08.437
- He'll come around.

34:10.657 --> 34:14.487
And I'm here for you.

34:16.532 --> 34:19.361
- We'll figure this out.

34:24.018 --> 34:25.976
Okay.

34:27.587 --> 34:30.242
- Now, I'm going to be sending
a series of beeps.

34:30.285 --> 34:32.940
First very soft, inaudible.

34:32.983 --> 34:35.856
When you can hear the beeps,
let me know.

34:40.817 --> 34:43.603
- Wait, yes.

34:43.646 --> 34:47.215
I can hear it, yes.
- Good.

34:47.259 --> 34:52.177
Tell me, Peter,
can you hear my voice?

34:52.220 --> 34:57.443
- Oh, God.
Yes, I can.

34:57.486 --> 34:59.488
I can hear again.

35:02.535 --> 35:05.407
♪

35:05.451 --> 35:07.670
- She said that
she'll be his eyes,

35:07.714 --> 35:10.020
and he'll be her ears.

35:19.987 --> 35:23.164
- Ms. Garrett, I know
we've had our differences,

35:23.208 --> 35:27.125
but I'm very happy you approved
the hybrid O.R. down here.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.133
Sharon, if you would.

35:44.577 --> 35:48.189
You go behind my back and
get these token contributions

35:48.233 --> 35:49.973
for about a quarter
of the cost.

35:50.017 --> 35:52.933
The hospital is out millions
for your pet project.

35:52.976 --> 35:54.848
- The Board could have
refused the money.

35:54.891 --> 35:56.545
- No, it couldn't,
and you know that.

35:56.589 --> 35:58.156
These are some of
our biggest donors.

35:58.199 --> 36:01.550
They want a hybrid O.R.,
they get a hybrid O.R.

36:01.594 --> 36:03.987
You locked us in.

36:04.031 --> 36:07.077
Are you going to fight me
on every one of my decisions?

36:07.121 --> 36:09.558
- Depends on the decision.

36:09.602 --> 36:12.779
♪

36:12.822 --> 36:15.434
- Well, I'm glad I know
where we stand.

36:18.437 --> 36:21.483
Our Chief of Emergency
Medicine, Dr. Stohl.

36:21.527 --> 36:22.919
Very much your man.

36:22.963 --> 36:25.313
- I think Dr. Stohl
is very much is own man.

36:25.357 --> 36:28.273
- I have not been happy
with his performance of late.

36:28.316 --> 36:30.449
We're not going to
renew his contract.

36:30.492 --> 36:35.628
- Really, you'd
take this out on him?

36:35.671 --> 36:37.586
- Stay out of my way.

36:40.633 --> 36:47.030
♪

36:47.074 --> 36:49.859
- They don't start serving
for another hour.

36:49.903 --> 36:51.818
- Sit.

36:56.126 --> 36:59.826
- Hanger steak,
planked whitefish,

36:59.869 --> 37:03.482
and for vegetarians,
lentil and chickpea stew.

37:03.525 --> 37:06.180
- Thank you.

37:09.705 --> 37:13.361
- Dishes to try
for our reception.

37:13.405 --> 37:17.060
You take care of the venue,
I'll take care of the caterer.

37:17.104 --> 37:19.976
You know, eyes and ears.

37:20.020 --> 37:22.457
Here, try.

37:25.504 --> 37:28.376
- Mmm.
That's really good.

37:28.420 --> 37:30.160
- Mm-hmm.

37:30.204 --> 37:33.990
♪

37:34.034 --> 37:37.211
- Here you go, Dr. Rhodes.
- Thanks, man.

37:37.255 --> 37:39.344
Ava, hey.

37:39.387 --> 37:42.912
So I was--I was looking into
what you were talking about,

37:42.956 --> 37:47.090
Rochester, and you are right.
It is very cold.

37:47.134 --> 37:50.268
- Yeah, so anyway,

37:50.311 --> 37:53.053
I told the Board I was going
to stay here at Med.

37:56.839 --> 37:59.364
- Yeah, I mean,
if the program is a success,

37:59.407 --> 38:02.802
then it could be
a very big deal.

38:02.845 --> 38:05.587
- It's a better career move
than Mayo.

38:07.328 --> 38:09.765
- Exactly.
- Okay.

38:09.809 --> 38:12.768
